The paper discusses machine learning black boxes and the need for interpretable explanations, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also proposes a novel technique for hiding biases in classifiers, which involves adversarial attacks, and evaluates the technique using real-world datasets, which falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), cryptography and security (cs.CR), cybernetics (cs.CY), and computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV).
